<pre class="bz_comment_text">It would be nice if we could fix issues like these wholesale, but it's not so clear-cut; e.g.

  <a href="https://github.com/OpenRC/openrc/pull/156">https://github.com/OpenRC/openrc/pull/156</a>

In the meantime, it's still a good idea to update the init scripts because people copy around stop() and reload() functions without any regard for what they're doing. Even if OpenRC was able to check the command name against the PID, there are plenty of copy/pasted stop() functions that don't pass the command name to s-s-d. Having bulletproof examples in the tree provides another layer of defense against the issue.</pre>
